, a stunning <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../496/78496.xml">
natural arch</link>, is located a short drive from Antofagasta.</p>
<p>

<link>
Pan de Azúcar National Park</link> is a park where sea and desert meet.</p>

</sec>
<sec>
<st>
 Norte Chico </st>
<p>

<image location="right" width="200px" src="Tololo_a.JPG" type="thumb">
</image>

The Andes of <region wordnetid="108630039" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../557/10163557.xml">
Norte Chico</link></location>
</region>
 are home to many of the highest volcanoes in the world, the highlight being <mountain wordnetid="109359803" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../966/1261966.xml">
Ojos del Salado</link></mountain>
. Apart from Ojos del Salado and the rest of the volcanoes, attractions in this portion of the Andes include <area wordnetid="108497294" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../624/8249624.xml">
Nevado Tres Cruces National Park</link></area>
 and <lake wordnetid="109328904" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../855/8824855.xml">
Laguna Verde</link></lake>
. </p>
<p>

Norte Chico boasts some of the best beaches and coastal resorts in the country, such as <link>
Bahía Inglesa</link> and those of <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_district wordnetid="108491826" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<municipality wordnetid="108626283" confidence="0.8">
<settlement wordnetid="108672562" confidence="0.8">
